t\t\t\t\t<div class=\"elementor-column elementor-col-100 elementor-top-column elementor-element elementor-element-93661ba\" data-id=\"93661ba\" data-element_type=\"column\">\n\t\t\t<div class=\"elementor-column-wrap elementor-element-populated\">\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\t<div class=\"elementor-widget-wrap\">\n\t\t\t\t\t\t<div class=\"elementor-element elementor-element-83e39d8 elementor-widget elementor-widget-text-editor\" data-id=\"83e39d8\" data-element_type=\"widget\" data-widget_type=\"text-editor.default\">\n\t\t\t\t<div class=\"elementor-widget-container\">\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t<div class=\"elementor-text-editor elementor-clearfix\">\n\t\t\t\t<p><strong>Basics<\/strong><\/p><ul><li>Definition: Hernia Through the Femoral Canal<\/li><li>More Common in Women, Inguinal Hernia Still Most Common Overall<\/li><li><strong>Highest Risk of Strangulation<\/strong> (40% Present Emergently)<\/li><\/ul><p><strong>Treatment<\/strong><\/p><ul><li>Tx: Repair <strong>All<\/strong> (Open or Laparoscopic)<ul><li>Open Procedure: <strong>McVay<\/strong> &amp; Divide <strong>Inguinal Ligament<\/strong> (To Reduce Bowel)<\/li><\/ul><\/li><\/ul>\t\t\t\t\t<\/div>\n\t\t\t\t\t\t<\/div>\n\t\t\t\t<\/div>\n\t\t\t\t\t\t<\/div>\n\t\t\t\t\t<\/div>\n\t\t<\/div>\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t<\/div>\n\t\t\t\t\t<\/div>\n\t\t<\/section>\n\t\t\t\t<section class=\"elementor-section elementor-top-section elementor-element elementor-element-5fb86c4 elementor-section-stretched elementor-section-boxed elementor-section-height-default elementor-section-height-default\" data-id=\"5fb86c4\" data-element_type=\"section\" data-settings=\"{&quot;stretch_section&quot;:&quot;section-stretched&quot;}\">\n\t\t\t\t\t\t<div class=\"elementor-container elementor-column-gap-default\">\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\t<div class=\"elementor-row\">\n\t\t\t\t\t<div class=\"elementor-column elementor-col-100 elementor-top-column elementor-element elementor-element-fcbf15c\" data-id=\"fcbf15c\" data-element_type=\"column\">\n\t\t\t<div class=\"elementor-column-wrap